Twitter can be used as a tool to evaluate start-up performance and provide valuable insights to investors. The sentiment analysis results revealed that the sentiment expressed on Twitter related to start-ups can provide a useful indication of their future performance. Investors can use these insights to make informed decisions about investing in start-ups. However, it is essential to consider the limitations of sentiment analysis, such as potential biases in the data collection and analysis process. Overall, this study provides insights into the role of Twitter in providing insights to investors on start-up performance.
